OL,3,CAs Delhi chokes after Diwali, India
OL,4,Ctrials artificial rain to clear
OL,5,Cpollution
OL,7,FBy the next morning, much of the city
OL,8,Fwas shrouded in toxic smog. Visibility
OL,9,Fdropped sharply, and residents
OL,10,Fcomplained of irritation in the eyes
OL,11,Fand throat.
OL,13,FHospitals reported a marked increase
OL,14,Fin cases of asthma, bronchitis, and
OL,15,Fother respiratory distress,
OL,16,Fparticularly among children and the
OL,17,Felderly. Health experts warn that
OL,18,Fprolonged exposure to such pollution
OL,19,Fsignificantly raises the risk of
OL,20,Fchronic lung and heart diseases.
